I'm going to start journalling my progress as I grind on Matchbox in. I'll add onto it as my rank increases.

I'm doing this both to be aware of my progress, and to maybe encourage others to do the same. I'm inspired by Smashmate's success in helping players grow in skill.

Earlier this week I got from 1500 to 1515 on the ranking by beating a Sonic Player, rematching them and beating them again.

Sets were both 2-0. I'm feeling more comfortable with the Sonic mu and not panicking or throwing out unsafe options as much.

Today I went from 1515 to 1531.

Today was a bit of an imperfect session, but in the end I came up on top.

I lost 0-2 to both a ZSS and Link player, but won three 2-0's in a row to improve my ranking. I played a Fox twice, then beat someone playing Random (Luigi/Simon).
